                <head>No. 447.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Smyth</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 14, 1880</date>. (Received May
                        19.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the pleasure to say to you that the
                    legislature of Liberia has adopted a resolution as to the prospective settlement
                    of the claim of the United States Government for ordnance, &amp;c.</p>
                <p>The following resolution, passed by the legislature of 1879–’80, was approved
                    January 17, 1880: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Upon the settlement of the postal claim against this republic, the whole
                            of the one-tenth of the revenue or moneys accruing therefrom shall be
                            paid in regular quarterly installments to the United States minister
                            resident, on account of the United States claims before mentioned; any
                            laws or parts of laws to the contrary notwithstanding.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JNO. H. SMYTH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
